    "This resembles the real-world mobility case where an individual would have a primary and a secondary home, and would frequently visit both, in contrast to moving from one location to the next.",
    "Here, we focus on publications as a marker of the position of an author.",
    "This could result in a \"ping-pong\" effect [55] where the author would frequently oscillate between two or more locations in a manner dictated by the chronological ordering of the publications in each domain.",
    "Here we have shown that such an effect is limited: the characteristic timescale of topic-switching is 1.5 years, significantly larger than the inter-article time of 0.53 years (Fig S5a).",
